18:04.818 --> 18:06.417
Right. {LAUGHS}

18:06.419 --> 18:08.519
Okay.

18:08.521 --> 18:10.588
The kids can
have it with dinner.
It will be divine.

18:10.590 --> 18:12.123
Speaking of dinner,

18:12.125 --> 18:13.091
it's time to pick
up the lobsters.

18:13.093 --> 18:14.225
GRACE: Yes. Okay.

18:14.227 --> 18:15.760
I've got the bikes all ready.

18:15.762 --> 18:18.262
Unfortunately, Wade,
we do not have a spare,

18:18.264 --> 18:20.131
so you can stay here
and clean my dinghy.

18:20.133 --> 18:22.800
No, no.
Honey, take my trike.

18:24.336 --> 18:27.105
I'm gonna do
a little gardening.

18:27.107 --> 18:28.473
Gracie, help your
father at the market.

18:28.475 --> 18:30.141
Of course.

18:31.743 --> 18:33.277
VIRGIL: Bringing alcohol
up in my house.

18:33.279 --> 18:34.512
SIMON: He doesn't
know us like that.

18:34.514 --> 18:35.646
{WHISPERING} You hid my stuff?
No.

18:35.648 --> 18:37.748
When they came, you hid it?
No!

18:37.750 --> 18:39.550
I was wondering,
because I got there,
and nothing was in its place.

18:39.552 --> 18:41.119
I was just organizing it.

18:41.121 --> 18:42.186
You organized it
right out of sight.

18:42.188 --> 18:43.354
Let's go
to the market.

18:43.356 --> 18:44.689
Let's go.
Let's go to the market.

18:44.691 --> 18:46.157
Let's go, Peeples!

18:50.195 --> 18:51.395
Think they got
fresh lobsters in today.

18:51.397 --> 18:53.898
Ah, I hope so.

18:53.900 --> 18:55.833
WADE: You know, I noticed
it looked like rain
on my way in here.

18:59.238 --> 19:00.838
What?

19:00.840 --> 19:02.707
GRACE: Uh, we don't say that.

19:02.709 --> 19:05.309
It's sort of
a family jinx thing.

19:05.311 --> 19:07.578
We never say it's
going to "you know,"

19:07.580 --> 19:10.314
because then it
definitely will.

19:10.316 --> 19:13.618
Sorry. It doesn't look
like rain. I take it back.

19:13.620 --> 19:15.720
You can't take it back,
Wade, because it's
already out there.

19:15.722 --> 19:17.188
Raincoats, everyone.

19:17.190 --> 19:20.291
No, no, no.
I take it back.

19:20.293 --> 19:22.426
I stand by my
reverse of the curse.

19:22.428 --> 19:23.794
All right?
It's not gonna rain.

19:26.798 --> 19:29.200
Rain-jinxed the whole weekend.

19:47.386 --> 19:50.721
These are beautiful.
Put them on ice for me.

19:53.525 --> 19:55.560
You getting some
dessert for us?

19:55.562 --> 19:56.561
GLORIA: Why not?
MEG: Mmm-hmm.

20:04.770 --> 20:06.370
Grace Peeples!

20:07.940 --> 20:09.607
{CHUCKLES} In the house!
Skip.

20:09.609 --> 20:11.209
Hi.

20:11.211 --> 20:12.643
How are you?
I'm fantastic.

20:12.645 --> 20:14.212
Wow.

20:14.214 --> 20:15.379
Oh, this is my boyfriend,
Wade Walker.

20:15.381 --> 20:17.248
Skip Snyder.
Nice to meet you.

20:17.250 --> 20:18.549
VIRGIL: Uh, Grace?

20:18.551 --> 20:20.718
Yeah. Will I see
you at Moby Dick Day?

20:20.720 --> 20:21.986
Wouldn't miss it.
Okay. Good.

20:21.988 --> 20:23.287
I'll be right back, Wade.

20:24.356 --> 20:25.489
You a friend of
Virgil Peeples?

20:25.491 --> 20:26.724
No. We dated.

20:27.859 --> 20:28.960
You dated
Virgil Peeples?

20:28.962 --> 20:30.795
No, of course not.

20:30.797 --> 20:33.464
I was like,
"I didn't know you
got down like that."

20:33.466 --> 20:35.533
I dated Grace.
She was incredible.

20:35.535 --> 20:38.402
So passionate.

20:38.404 --> 20:40.738
Really hurt so good!
{CHUCKLES}

20:40.740 --> 20:42.673
Virgil Peeples'
daughter Grace?

20:42.675 --> 20:45.443
Yeah. Little chocolate
drop right over there.
Mmm mmm mmm!

20:45.445 --> 20:46.677
Hey! Martin!

20:51.750 --> 20:52.717
Hello.

20:53.952 --> 20:55.786
Chump.

20:55.788 --> 20:57.655
I took Grace
from him, and he's
still sour-graping.

20:58.657 --> 21:00.524
{CHUCKLING}

21:00.526 --> 21:03.761
You're a lucky man.
Lord have mercy!

21:03.763 --> 21:06.297
I used to... Mmm mmm!

21:11.470 --> 21:12.703
You're blessed.

21:18.644 --> 21:19.844
Bananas?

21:19.846 --> 21:21.012
Is it ripe enough for you?

21:22.614 --> 21:23.514
Okay.

21:32.591 --> 21:33.557
WOMAN: Will I see you tonight?

21:34.693 --> 21:36.494
I'll be there.

21:36.496 --> 21:38.396
And you're sure
Daphne doesn't know?

21:38.398 --> 21:39.964
Doesn't have a clue.

21:39.966 --> 21:41.565
Could be fun
to include her.

21:41.567 --> 21:43.834
You're kidding, right?

21:43.836 --> 21:46.537
You have to ease
her into it, Virgil.

21:46.539 --> 21:49.307
Let's just keep this
between me and you.

21:49.309 --> 21:50.408
Don't be such a tight-ass.

21:54.479 --> 21:55.846
I'll see you tonight.

22:02.921 --> 22:03.654
{REGISTER BEEPING}

22:05.023 --> 22:05.890
CASHIER: $206.19.

22:08.593 --> 22:10.361
Oh, shit.

22:12.531 --> 22:13.664
I don't have any money.

22:13.666 --> 22:15.399
What's the holdup?

22:15.401 --> 22:16.734
He doesn't have any money,
Mrs. Davis.

22:16.736 --> 22:17.968
Huh?

22:17.970 --> 22:20.838
He doesn't have
any money!

22:20.840 --> 22:25.343
Oh, how sad.
The colored boy
doesn't have any money.

22:25.345 --> 22:27.511
I know Where's the Beef
didn't just call
me "a colored boy."

22:31.950 --> 22:33.784
That's a lot of
walk-around money.

22:33.786 --> 22:34.952
You've probably
got Oprah dollars.

22:34.954 --> 22:36.654
Keep the change, Wade.

22:36.656 --> 22:38.689
It's not that
I don't have money.

22:38.691 --> 22:41.492
It's misplaced right now.
I don't know
what happened to it.

22:41.494 --> 22:44.428
It's probably on the...
I could have left my
wallet on the jitney.

22:45.664 --> 22:47.631
Damn.

22:47.633 --> 22:50.368
Well, they won't
help themselves.

22:53.638 --> 22:55.005
Hey, babe.
Hey.

22:56.041 --> 22:58.676
So, Skip was interesting.

22:58.678 --> 23:00.745
Yeah.
He's great, isn't he?

23:00.747 --> 23:03.714
So great.

23:03.716 --> 23:05.149
He said the craziest
thing, though.
What's that?

23:05.151 --> 23:06.884
He said that y'all
two used to date.

23:06.886 --> 23:08.419
Yeah. That's right.

23:08.421 --> 23:09.520
For real?
Yeah.

23:11.523 --> 23:13.724
Don't you think
you should have
said something to me?

23:13.726 --> 23:16.494
What... Do I know about
every single woman
that you've dated?

23:16.496 --> 23:17.895
No, you don't.
Okay.

23:17.897 --> 23:19.597
But if I had
dated Harriet Tubman,

23:19.599 --> 23:20.998
I probably would
have said something.

23:21.000 --> 23:23.033
If I was texting
Madam C.J. Walker.

23:23.035 --> 23:24.468
Wade...

23:24.470 --> 23:24.969
Or Shirley Chisholm.

23:30.675 --> 23:31.976
So this is about age?
Yeah.

23:31.978 --> 23:33.511
He is a brilliant doctor.

23:33.513 --> 23:34.745
I'm sure he is.
He probably gave

23:34.747 --> 23:36.680
Adam and Eve
their first physicals.

23:36.682 --> 23:41.051
Wow! An ageist.
I thought you were
more mature than that.

23:41.053 --> 23:42.486
I should be more mature?
Yeah.

23:42.488 --> 23:44.088
Like Martin?

23:44.090 --> 23:46.424
Who told you about Martin?

23:46.426 --> 23:49.860
Oh, I met Uncle Ben and
Bojangles up in there...
Oh. {CHUCKLES} Wow.

23:49.862 --> 23:51.662
...at the National Black
History Month Caucus.

23:52.697 --> 23:54.565
It was all up in there.

23:54.567 --> 23:57.468
All your little grandpa
exes came dancing up
out of the crypt.

23:57.470 --> 23:58.569
GRACE: Enough.

23:58.571 --> 23:59.737
<i>Like Thriller.</i>

23:59.739 --> 24:00.538
{VOCALIZING}

24:12.951 --> 24:15.753
Got me on this damn bike
like I'm three years old.

24:17.756 --> 24:19.757
Who else you go
out with, Grace?

24:19.759 --> 24:21.125
Benjamin Banneker?
W.E.B. Du Bois?

24:21.127 --> 24:23.561
GRACE: Okay, Wade.

24:23.563 --> 24:26.464
WADE: George Washington
Carver? You and Booker T.
was a thing?

